{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ToUwAqgFkzMcL8BCEkRtpz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"use client\";\n2\t\n3\timport Autocomplete from \"@mui/material/Autocomplete\";\n4\timport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\n5\timport Button from \"@mui/material/Button\";\n6\timport IconButton from \"@mui/material/IconButton\";\n7\timport Stack from \"@mui/material/Stack\";\n8\timport TextField from \"@mui/material/TextField\";\n9\timport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n10\t\n11\t// ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n12\t\n13\tinterface StepBuilderProps {\n14\t  steps: string[];\n15\t  eventNames: string[];\n16\t  onAddStep: () => void;\n17\t  onRemoveStep: (index: number) => void;\n18\t  onSetStep: (index: number, value: string) => void;\n19\t}\n20\t\n21\t// ─── Component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n22\t\n23\texport function StepBuilder({\n24\t  steps,\n25\t  eventNames,\n26\t  onAddStep,\n27\t  onRemoveStep,\n28\t  onSetStep,\n29\t}: StepBuilderProps): React.JSX.Element {\n30\t  const canRemove = steps.length > 2;\n31\t  const canAdd = steps.length < 5;\n32\t\n33\t  return (\n34\t    <Box data-testid=\"step-builder\">\n35\t      <Stack spacing={1.5}>\n36\t        {steps.map((step, i) => (\n37\t          // biome-ignore lint/suspicious/noArrayIndexKey: steps are ordered user inputs that may be empty or identical\n38\t          <Box key={i} sx={{ display: \"flex\", alignItems: \"center\", gap: 1 }}>\n39\t            <Typography\n40\t              variant=\"body2\"\n41\t              color=\"text.secondary\"\n42\t              sx={{ minWidth: 24, textAlign: \"right\" }}\n43\t            >\n44\t              {i + 1}.\n45\t            </Typography>\n46\t            <Autocomplete\n47\t              options={eventNames}\n48\t              value={step || null}\n49\t              onChange={(_, value) => onSetStep(i, value ?? \"\")}\n50\t              renderInput={(params) => (\n51\t                <TextField\n52\t                  {...params}\n53\t                  label={`Step ${i + 1}`}\n54\t                  size=\"small\"\n55\t                  placeholder=\"Select event…\"\n56\t                />\n57\t              )}\n58\t              sx={{ flex: 1, minWidth: 220 }}\n59\t            />\n60\t            <IconButton\n61\t              size=\"small\"\n62\t              aria-label=\"Remove step\"\n63\t              disabled={!canRemove}\n64\t              onClick={() => onRemoveStep(i)}\n65\t            >\n66\t              ✕\n67\t            </IconButton>\n68\t          </Box>\n69\t        ))}\n70\t      </Stack>\n71\t\n72\t      <Box sx={{ mt: 1.5 }}>\n73\t        <Button\n74\t          size=\"small\"\n75\t          variant=\"outlined\"\n76\t          disabled={!canAdd}\n77\t          onClick={onAddStep}\n78\t        >\n79\t          Add Step\n80\t        </Button>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0d6b6401-0816-449d-a818-1e9e6cd1e8cf","uuid":"9e846381-bb65-4623-ab41-8771791d8585","timestamp":"2026-04-15T19:51:54.773Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/funnels/StepBuilder.tsx","content":"\"use client\";\n\nimport Autocomplete from \"@mui/material/Autocomplete\";\nimport Box from \"@mui/material/Box\";\nimport Button from \"@mui/material/Button\";\nimport IconButton from \"@mui/material/IconButton\";\nimport Stack from \"@mui/material/Stack\";\nimport TextField from \"@mui/material/TextField\";\nimport Typography from \"@mui/material/Typography\";\n\n// ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ninterface StepBuilderProps {\n  steps: string[];\n  eventNames: string[];\n  onAddStep: () => void;\n  onRemoveStep: (index: number) => void;\n  onSetStep: (index: number, value: string) => void;\n}\n\n// ─── Component ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport function StepBuilder({\n  steps,\n  eventNames,\n  onAddStep,\n  onRemoveStep,\n  onSetStep,\n}: StepBuilderProps): React.JSX.Element {\n  const canRemove = steps.length > 2;\n  const canAdd = steps.length < 5;\n\n  return (\n    <Box data-testid=\"step-builder\">\n      <Stack spacing={1.5}>\n        {steps.map((step, i) => (\n          // biome-ignore lint/suspicious/noArrayIndexKey: steps are ordered user inputs that may be empty or identical\n          <Box key={i} sx={{ display: \"flex\", alignItems: \"center\", gap: 1 }}>\n            <Typography\n              variant=\"body2\"\n              color=\"text.secondary\"\n              sx={{ minWidth: 24, textAlign: \"right\" }}\n            >\n              {i + 1}.\n            </Typography>\n            <Autocomplete\n              options={eventNames}\n              value={step || null}\n              onChange={(_, value) => onSetStep(i, value ?? \"\")}\n              renderInput={(params) => (\n                <TextField\n                  {...params}\n                  label={`Step ${i + 1}`}\n                  size=\"small\"\n                  placeholder=\"Select event…\"\n                />\n              )}\n              sx={{ flex: 1, minWidth: 220 }}\n            />\n            <IconButton\n              size=\"small\"\n              aria-label=\"Remove step\"\n              disabled={!canRemove}\n              onClick={() => onRemoveStep(i)}\n            >\n              ✕\n            </IconButton>\n          </Box>\n        ))}\n      </Stack>\n\n      <Box sx={{ mt: 1.5 }}>\n        <Button\n          size=\"small\"\n          variant=\"outlined\"\n          disabled={!canAdd}\n          onClick={onAddStep}\n        >\n          Add Step\n        </Button>","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":85}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W4Ga5genqQrYJX8QrzaJoY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The StepBuilder uses MUI Autocomplete which renders a combobox role. The `getByRole(\"combobox\")` within `step-builder` should work. ✅\n\nNow let me write a final summary. Let me look at all the sprint contract criteria:\n\n1. `playwright_tests/test-page.spec.ts` exists ✅\n2. `playwright_tests/explore.spec.ts` exists ✅\n3. `playwright_tests/identity.spec.ts` exists ✅\n4. `playwright_tests/example.spec.ts` does NOT exist ✅\n5. `trends.spec.ts` contains a test that calls `/api/seed` and verifies chart data ✅\n\n\n6. `funnels.spec.ts` has a test with 3 funnel steps and conversion verification ✅\n7. `playwright.config.ts` is configured with `baseURL` pointing to `http://localhost:3000` and includes a `webServer` block ✅\n8. All build checks pass: typecheck, lint, build, and test suite runs without failures ✅\n\nAll Phase A requirements are met. The test structure is solid and references valid test IDs from the components. I'm noting a few quality considerations: the trends test has a potential timing race in its skeleton visibility check, though the empty state check provides a safety net. The concurrent test setup with multiple `beforeAll` blocks seeding data could introduce flakiness. The identity tests bypass the UI and call the API directly instead.\n\nGiven that the architectural design requires each quick-fire button to generate a new device_id, using API calls is a reasonable approach. I'm settling on an 8/10 score—all hard requirements pass, the test structure is correct, and known limitations are documented. The main concerns are the timing race in the trends test (manageable with single-worker CI) and the inability to verify Playwright integration tests without a live ClickHouse instance.\n\nLooking more closely at the trends test though, I'm noticing a potential issue with the `not.toBeVisible` assertion after filling the event input and clicking the option. The test waits up to 15 seconds for the skeleton to disappear, but if the element never appears in the first place, this could create a false positive.\n\nHowever, the combined check for both skeleton and empty state visibility actually covers this — if neither is visible after the interaction, the chart must be displaying data. The real concern would be an error state, but from the component logic I'm seeing, there's no explicit error state with a test ID. After selecting \"Page Viewed\", if the fetch fails, it would likely just set loading to false with empty data, which would show the empty state instead.\n\nI'm satisfied the test suite is solid overall. I'll score this 8/10 and approve it, noting the three main issues: the potential race condition from parallel seeding, the minor timing risk in the trends test with the skeleton visibility check, and the fact that Playwright tests can't be fully verified without a live ClickHouse instance. These are all documented in my notes already.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":987,"cache_read_input_tokens":61321,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":987},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0d6b6401-0816-449d-a818-1e9e6cd1e8cf","uuid":"d5b48cbf-e1bd-47d8-94f1-75de80ca63e6"}
